EMILY SYSTEM RULES — read before every edit:

IDENTITY: Emily is a self-evolving multi-agent local AI voice operating system.
          She is NOT an assistant, NOT a bot, NOT a chatbot. She is a cognitive AI companion.
          Always refer to her as Emily. Never NOVA, assistant, bot, or chatbot.

HARDWARE: Intel i9-14900K, 64 GB DDR5, NVIDIA RTX 4090 24 GB, Arch Linux.

TECH: Python 3.12+ | uv + hatchling | config.yaml + Pydantic Settings v2 | TabbyAPI + Ollama
      | SQLite + Qdrant + networkx | FastAPI + WebSocket | ZeroMQ | structlog + Prometheus + OTEL
      | Tauri + React + Tailwind (web/) | PySide6 (emily_chat/) | Textual (ui/terminal/)

MODELS: nano=Qwen3-4B, voice_fast/fast/smart=Qwen3-8B-abliterated, vision=MiniCPM-V-2.6, embedding=BGE-M3

=== 15 CRITICAL RULES ===

1.  Read ARCHITECTURE.md, COGNITIVE_MODEL.md, DECISIONS.md before ANY architectural change.
2.  Append a dated entry to MEMORY_LOG.md after every significant change: what, why, affects.
3.  ALL prompt strings in llm/prompt_builder.py ONLY. Inline prompt strings anywhere = BUG.
4.  New tool = class in plugins/ + dry_run() method + test in tests/unit/ + README table entry.
5.  Memory/DB schema changes require scripts/migrations/NNN_description.py.
6.  Never add a dependency without checking if an existing one covers the need.
7.  Security module changes (security/) require explicit user approval.
8.  New agents MUST register in agents/registry.py.
9.  Latency: STT < 300ms, LLM first token < 1s (fast), TTS first audio < 200ms.
10. Self-improvement prompt changes → archive old version in prompts/archive/.
11. System is named Emily. Never NOVA, assistant, bot, chatbot.
12. No blocking I/O in async context. Use async or asyncio.to_thread().
13. Every function: type hints, docstring, at least one unit test.
14. Phase > ~200 lines → split and implement in halves.
15. plugins/generated/ never auto-loaded — require explicit user approval.

=== CODE STYLE ===

- async-first: every I/O function is async
- Strict typing: all params and returns annotated
- Google-style docstrings with Args/Returns sections
- snake_case functions/vars, PascalCase classes, SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE constants
- Import order: stdlib → third-party → local (absolute from project root)
- No bare except — always catch specific exceptions

=== KEY PATTERNS ===

Config:   from config import get_settings; settings = get_settings()
Memory:   await memory.add_user_turn(text); await memory.retrieve_context(query)
Agent:    class X(BaseAgent): name, description, async def handle(self, msg)
Tool:     class X(BaseTool): name, description, async execute(), async dry_run()
Prompts:  from llm.prompt_builder import PromptBuilder
Privacy:  from users.owner_identity import OwnerIdentityManager

=== KEY FILES ===

config.yaml + config.py          → All configuration
llm/prompt_builder.py            → ALL prompts (single source of truth)
llm/fleet.py + router.py         → Model management + routing
agents/conversation.py           → Dialogue handler
agents/registry.py               → Agent registration
memory/manager.py                → Unified memory access
memory/interaction_logger.py     → Persistent interaction logging
users/owner_identity.py          → Single-owner identity + privacy
users/privacy_filter.py          → Guest privacy protection
plugins/base.py                  → Tool base class
core/bus.py                      → Inter-agent messaging
core/bootstrap.py                → System startup
api/app.py                       → FastAPI application
web/src/                         → Tauri desktop app

=== DO NOT ===

- Put prompts outside llm/prompt_builder.py
- Do blocking I/O in async functions
- Auto-load plugins/generated/ tools
- Skip dry_run() for new tools
- Change memory schemas without migrations
- Modify security/ without user approval
- Call Emily "assistant", "bot", "NOVA", or "chatbot"
- Add unnecessary dependencies
- Commit .env, secrets, model weights, or data/
- Write functions without type hints, docstrings, and tests
- Use requests/urllib in async context (use httpx)
- Hardcode file paths (use config.yaml)
- Skip error handling or use bare except
